3. Pantheon relevance of radians

Radians are essentially angle normalized by radius.

They measure curvature per unit distance.

That means radians are the natural unit for:
	•	oscillations
	•	wave phase
	•	rotations
	•	orbital systems
	•	Fourier transforms
	•	neural oscillations
	•	signal timing

Many systems in nature operate in phase space measured in radians.

So if you’re building frameworks for pattern or signal reasoning, radians are often the natural coordinate system.

