6. Golden ratio doubled vs π

Golden ratio:

\phi = 1.6180339887...

Double it:

2\phi = 3.236067977...

π is:

\pi = 3.141592653...

Difference:

2\phi - \pi ≈ 0.094475

Relative difference:

\frac{0.094475}{\pi} ≈ 3\%

So they’re close but not special mathematically.

However they both appear frequently because:
	•	π governs circular geometry.
	•	φ governs recursive growth and optimization.

So they arise in different structural regimes.

